# Implementation Plan - Strictly Minimal Parent Task Data (v3)

This plan implements a "Structural Shell" pattern for parent tasks. All parent tasks, regardless of the entry point or strategy, will carry only the minimal data required for containment. Detailed metadata (Assignees, Reviewers, Descriptions, etc.) is strictly reserved for subtasks.

## Proposed Changes

### [query-builder.ts](file:///c:\VamsiKrishna\Github\Tusker-managment\src\lib\tasks\query-builder.ts)

Update the `isMinimal` selection to be the source of truth for all parent task representations.

#### [MODIFY] [query-builder.ts](file:///c:\VamsiKrishna\Github\Tusker-managment\src\lib\tasks\query-builder.ts)
- Refine the `isMinimal` selection (lines 4-15) to include only:
