### [tasks.service.ts](file:///c:\VamsiKrishna\Github\Tusker-managment\src\server\services\tasks.service.ts)

Enforce the minimal selection across all service methods whenever a parent task is fetched.

#### [MODIFY] [tasks.service.ts](file:///c:\VamsiKrishna\Github\Tusker-managment\src\server\services\tasks.service.ts)
- **Root Fetches**: Update `_fetchProjectRoot` and `_fetchWorkspaceFilter` to always use `getTaskSelect(..., true)` when `isParent` is part of the filter or when fetching structural shells.
- **Hierarchy Management**: Update `_fetchFilteredHierarchy` to use the minimal selection for all structural tasks in the tree.
- **Strict Distinction**:
    - **Parent Fetch**: `getTaskSelect(mode, true)`
    - **Subtask Fetch**: `getTaskSelect(mode, false)`
- **Expansion Logic**: Even in `expandSubtasks` or `batchExpand`, if the returned items are themselves parents (nested levels), they will also use the minimal structure.

## Rules & Constraints

- **Parents = Shells**: No relational objects (`assignee`, `reviewer`, `createdBy`, `tag`) or heavy text (`description`) will exist on parent tasks in any JSON response.
- **Subtasks = Detail**: Subtasks carry the full relational data required for the detail rows and Kanban cards.
- **No Exceptions**: This rule applies even during "Detail Expansion" if that expansion involves parent structural elements.

